    "These two metrics are calculated to compute the dissimilarity between the embedded signature and the extracted one after applying different attacks to the marked content.",
    "In fact, the BER provides the percentage of erroneous bits during the transmission, and it is given by the following equation where S is the original signature, S' is the extracted one, i Ber i is the number of bit in error, and i Btrans i is the total number of transmitted bits:B E R(S, S) = i Ber i i Btrans i (6)The NC calculates the similarity between two media.",
